{"author":{"id":"458c2786e2fb21c7f2463be283bdb1d457c6c22ed9854985782318ab918e2e3f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1510867484,"nonce":"DchzUrC0zNCdFQDfMjhCEh7EX2Y=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNzQ2Njg5MjU=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1581","origin":"github"},"title":"MultiQC for featurecounts fails when using default dataset names","message":"It seems that when metadata column names for featureCounts summary output has commas (','), MultiQC will fail. This line (https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/master/tools/multiqc/multiqc.xml#L111) attempts to do some cleanup on the metadata column names and reinsert them back into the output (they seem to have been scrubbed here (https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/master/tools/featurecounts/featurecounts.xml#L100). MultiQC requires that the file be intact (as output from featureCounts) and so the MultiQC wrapper must \"put it back together\". However, the substitute of tabs for comma's causes problems.\n\nAs an aside, I've noticed that this same error is made elsewhere in Galaxy (e.g. the display of tabular data with commas in the metadata column names is messed up as the commas have been changed to tabs). See https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy/issues/5026.","files":null}]}